title: Canadian housing starts decline 2.5% in September: CMHC
text:
Canadian housing starts decline 2.5% in September: CMHC

Economic Indicators 15 minutes ago (Oct 08, 2019 08:46AM ET)

Canadian housing starts decline 2.5% in September: CMHC TORONTO (Reuters) - Canadian housing starts in September fell from the previous month as groundbreaking dropped by more than 9% on single-detached urban homes, data from the national housing agency showed on Tuesday. The seasonally adjusted annualized rate of housing starts fell 2.5% to 221,202 units from a revised 226,871 units in August, the Canadian Mortgage and Housing Corporation (CMHC) said. Economists had expected starts to fall to 214,500 units.
